Name: POH YONG LING (FU YONGLING)
Content:
Abit embarrassing to share but thought would be a good reminder to myself that 100% is possible, 100% of the time with massive actions. 

Had gotten my driving license back in 2014, but never drive much n somehow the longer I donâ€™t drive, the more fear I have, n more resistant I had towards driving. 
Last year due to certain events, I set a new resolutions to be a safe n skilled driving. I signed up for refresher driving lessons with a private instructor but I was inconsistent in having the lessons n I didnâ€™t have much practice. So I didnâ€™t manage to achieve that goal. 

Fast forward to 2025, my new year resolutions remain the same to be a safe n skilled driver. 
N this year, I did something different. I went to rent car to practice driving. I visualize myself being a skillful driver. 
I got a close gf to agree to accompany me to practice driving. 

N today for the first time, I finally had the guts to drive Alfred n 2 kids from East to west to my sis place n back to the east safely. ğŸ˜†ğŸ¤£

Thankful to Alfred @alfredtohlegacy for giving me tips n warning along the way n the kids for being such patient passengers by keeping quiet to let me focus on the road. So quiet that they fell asleep on the way back. ğŸ˜

Small achievement unlocked â˜ºï¸

Name: ALVIN KEH
Content:
- GFriend's 10th Anniversary Concert (Part 2) -

The school bell rang.

For a moment, I thought I lost the bet as I didn't expect ã€ŠGlass Beadã€‹ to be the opening song to kickstart the 3 nights of concert.

Whether was it paying homage toã€ŠGo Go GFriend!ã€‹ , or simply being 1 of the "School Trilogy" songs, ã€ŠMe Gustas Tuã€‹ended up as the opening act.

As the concert progresses, I realized that this wasn't a trip to Seoul; but instead, a trip down the memory lane.

Just like every other Buddy, I too have a story with GFriend - one that is over a decade long.

It all started back in 2015......

I was barely 25.

I was 26 when I met GFriend as Mr. Pikachu for the very first time at theirã€ŠL.O.L. Showcaseã€‹ in Singapore.

I was 27 when I made an impromptu trip to Seoul to attend my very 1st Fan Sign event & Music Show.

I was 28 when I travelled all the way to Seoul for 3 days just to attend both nights of ã€ŠSeason of GFriendã€‹

I was 29 when I went for all 10 stops of ã€ŠGo Go GFriendã€‹ Asia Tour across 9 countries.

I was 30 when I last saw GFriend at a Fan Sign event in Seoul before Covid-19 restricted all our travelling plans.

I was 31 when GFriend made an announcement that they won't be renewing their respective contracts.

And then I made a wish.

"In the year 2025, I hope that GFriend will have a reunion for their 10th Anniversary"

I was 35 when it eventually came true.

Back to the present, at their concert, a video of their past MVs were played.

Before the start of the concert, I was prepared to cry; just like how I did when I attended SNSD's 10th Anniversary Fan Meet.

And then I realized, there wasn't any reason to.

As a Buddy, I managed to do everything that I wanted to - except for the fact that I missed all the events when they sang ã€ŠNeverlandã€‹ 

Rather than being emotional about how we had a hiatus & reuniting 4 years later, I was actually grateful that I had an incredible 6 years with them.

From ã€ŠSeason of Glassã€‹to ã€ŠSeason of Memoriesã€‹, I spent 40 Seasons with #GFriend

Content:
30 years on earth! I always had many milestones for this age, and well...

I dont have the relationship I want,
but I have the love I need.

I dont have the house I want, 
but I have the family I need. 

I dont have the money I want, 
but I have the freedom I need. 

I was a little sad to not have achieved all the forms of success I had wanted when I was in my 20s...but I realised what I do have is clarity of what's, and will continue to be, truly important to me for the rest of my life, and a good idea of how to spend the time I have on earth tending to these special things.

Content:

One of the biggest reasons why my clients, prospects or people that I talk to tend NOT to invest is because they are afraid of the volatility and fluctuations in the market.

While understandable, thatâ€™s also the MAIN reason why most donâ€™t reach their financial goals in life, on time :(

But no fear! In this post, Iâ€™ll be going through the top 5 things you need to understand if you want to know how to almost always WIN in the stock market.

#1 UNDERSTAND ASSETS
Identify asset classes and their respective nature. Over time, due to various factors (supply & demand, companies grow bigger), there will be a general uptrend.

#2 UNDERSTAND VOLATILITY
Volatility refers to fluctuations in value.
Standard deviation is used to measure the spread of returns.

Historical records show that the S&P500 follows a reasonably normal distribution; symmetric around the mean.

#3 NORMAL DISTRIBUTION... SO WHAT?
ALL ABOUT PROBABILITY

A normal distribution is also a probability distribution.
Rule of thumb: 68% of the yearly returns tend to fall within 1 standard deviation of the average return, 95% tend to fall within 2 standard deviation.

#4 UNDERSTAND VOLATILITY WITH NORMAL DISTRIBUTION

Therefore, assets usually fluctuate beyond the average market returns (8-10%), for better or for worse.

It has been shown that the longer the time horizon, the smaller the standard deviation. 
*Disclaimer: Standard deviation is merely used as a gauge, not to limit the range of market returns.

#5 UNDERSTAND NET RETURNS

It's true investments are never guaranteed.
However, the compounding effect is cumulative. If an average bull market cycle generates a total return of 268%, and the market crashes by 33% the following year, will you consider this a net gain or a net loss?
*Disclaimer: Assuming that you are invested in a well-diversified portfolio.

The biggest secret is your time in the market rather than timing the market.

#journalswithjared #valuecashcourse

Name: TAN WEI LONG, ROYSTON
Content:
Happy Chinese New Year! æ–°å¹´å¿«ä¹ï¼Sitting on to cash from your red packet? ğŸ§§ğŸ§§Here is something for you to ponder.

Many people hold large amounts of cash, thinking itâ€™s the safest way to protect their wealth. But the truth is, cash is a guaranteed way to lose money over time.

Hereâ€™s why:

1ï¸âƒ£ Inflation Erodes Purchasing Power
Imagine keeping $100,000 in cash for 10 years with an average inflation rate of 3%. That money would only have the purchasing power of about $74,000 in todayâ€™s terms. The longer you hold onto cash, the less it buys.

2ï¸âƒ£ Opportunity Cost
While your cash sits idle, investments in equities, real estate, or even bonds generate returns. Historically, the stock market has averaged 7-10% annually. Over decades, thatâ€™s a massive difference in wealth creation.

3ï¸âƒ£ Negative Real Returns
Even high-yield savings accounts barely keep up with inflation. If your money earns 2% interest but inflation is 4%, youâ€™re effectively losing 2% per year.

ğŸ’¡ So, whatâ€™s the solution?
Instead of hoarding cash, put it to work. A well-diversified investment strategy tailored to your goals can help grow your wealth and outpace inflation. Cash has its place for emergencies, but as a long-term investment? Itâ€™s a slow but certain loss.

How are you deploying your cash wisely? Letâ€™s discuss. #sgwealthplanner #financialfreedom #generationalwealth

Name: ZHANG JINGSHENG
Content:
ğŸ¶Sakedokoro Eizaburo @eizaburo_official the latest concept by the Shunsui Group. This new izakaya brings a refreshing take on Japanese drinking and dining culture.
 
Located inğŸ“ Fortune Centre, Eizaburo recreates the retro charm of Japanâ€™s shitamachi culture, known for its traditional working-class neighborhoods and warm hospitality. Embracing a no-frills concept, the restaurant uses disposable tableware and online ordering to keep costs low while maintaining quality.
 
Enjoy small plates such as:
Binchotan-grilled Yakitori from $2.90++
Fresh Sashimi and Sushi from $3.90++
Side dishes such as Potato Salad, Creamy Crab Croquette, and Wagyu Sagari Steak from $3.90++

Lunch highlights include towering Kaisen-dons, Unagi Bowls, and Curry Udon / Rice from $7.90++.
 
Raise a glass with drinks starting from $6.90 such as Ultra Fizzy Whisky Highball and Lemon Sour, Suntory Premium Malts Draft at $9.80++, Shochu bottles from $69++, and Junmai Daiginjo from $84++. Donâ€™t miss signature drinks like Baisu Sour and Sake with Oden Soup.
 
To maintain Eizaburoâ€™s image as a drinking spot, as well as its competitive prices, there are 9 commandments that are requested of diners to understand prior to their visit. These include rules such as a two-drink policy per person, 90-minute dining limit during peak hours and rules to ensure a comfortable dining experience for other diners.
 
Eizaburo offers 48 seats, including a private room for up to 12 guests (reservations from 8 pax). Time Sales will be offered once a day, at a random, surprise timing, featuring special dishes at unbeatable prices.
